The extension forwards a bearer token to the labeler, while product docs claim tokens are never sent to third parties. Align implementation and trust boundaries so credential handling is explicit, justified, and secure.

## Todo
- [x] Write failing tests or assertions for the current emit contract
- [x] Decide and implement the supported auth contract between extension and labeler
- [x] Remove unnecessary token forwarding or document it accurately if retained
- [x] Verify successful edits still trigger labels correctly
- [x] Update user-facing auth/privacy docs

## Summary of Changes
- Added explicit auth-contract coverage in `test/unit/background/message-router.test.ts` to assert:
  - successful edits still trigger labeler emits
  - only the access token is forwarded in `Authorization: Bearer ...`
  - refresh token material is not forwarded in emit payloads
- Confirmed current supported contract is to retain access-token forwarding to labeler emits, required for labeler-side token verification against user PDS.
- Updated `docs/guide/privacy.md` to explicitly state:
  - access tokens are sent to labeler emit endpoint when labeler integration is active
  - refresh tokens are never sent to the labeler
